===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*g/m/b-raŋ||strong; firm; tense}} or {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(d/t)aŋ||tense; tight}}, the latter which appears to be preferred based on more current research ({{zh-ref|Hill, 2019}}, p. 224); compare {{cog|bo|ཐང་པོ||tense; tight; firm}}, {{cog|my|တင်း||to tighten; to be tight}}.

Pronunciation 2 is the exopassive of pronunciation 1, literally “to be stretched” ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

